my step grandmothers son died months ago while i was pregnant they just came from florida to visit us and our baby and she mentioned how disappointed she was that i had not gotten in contact with them after his death i was mortified that i had forgotten to call or send something to them i said my being pregnant is no excuse for not contacting you after terries death i am so sorry for my horrible lack of understanding and compassion during your grief we were both crying and i hugged her afterwards but i still feel absolutely awful and ashamed of myself what can i do now after the fact to make up for that is there anything or should i leave my apology as it is and move on you apologized and sadly you can't go back in time and be more considerate trust me the grief doesn't end and there is plenty of time for you to be there for her now let her now how very much you want to be with her and be there for her tell her she can call you day or night if she needs to talk also ask her specifically what can i do for you call her keep in touch with her that is all you can do Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Kodocha Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Knots Landing Melanie Wilkes Le Malade imaginaire Pitaten Pregnancy Ocean's Twelve Grief Leo Wyatt Beetle in an Anthill Cindy Sheehan Friends Days of our Lives The Amber Spyglass Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Father's Day (Doctor Who) EastEnders Brother Bear John Sheridan (Babylon 5) The Unquiet Dead Futurama (TV series - season 5) Night (book) Phoebe Halliwell Virginia Lewis (The 10th Kingdom) Theory of conduct Social rule Sami Brady History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Abortion debate Wolfrider Parsifal The Smoking Room Mystique (comics) Haven (TNG episode) Fruits Basket Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Queen of Wands The Silence of the Lambs Jewish bereavement Shaggy dog story Plame affair Autism John Carter (ER) Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Miscarriage God Emperor of Dune Coming of Age (TNG episode)